		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">donations<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: donations";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 10th 1:46 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1110480375649658082&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1110480375649658082&num=16&post=1&replyto=1110480375649658082"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1110480375649658082></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=170443"><span id=>flashheart</span></a><b><span id=></span></b><br />12 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=flashheart&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;  When asking for buffs in POK, I try to always make a donation when I can.  But what is the correct amount to donate?  I have never played a caster past level 10, so I do not know what components there are to spells and what they are worth.  Any advice would be greatly appreciated.  By the way, I am a level 31 monk on Bristlebane, and have some pretty decent gear, but nothing spectacular, and about 500 pp to my name.  Also, is there a difference between the servers; i.e. buffs are worth more on Fironia Vie or Stromm versus the others.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Work is the curse of the drinking class. - Oscar Wilde</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >16 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Thu, Mar 10th 2:09 PM2005 </span><span id="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=1&mid=1110480375649658082&num=16&post=1&replyto=1110481719908896436"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=1110481719908896436></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=247125"><span id=Scholar>Jiggidyjay of the Seven Seas</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="50" width="50" src="/uf/Jiggidyjay/Flippie_20_Spammer.gif"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*"/><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />1668 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.52]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Jiggidyjay&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>Every server has it's own economy and own &quot;rules&quot; (more like standards) on donations. The amount that you donate will probably fluctuate greatly with your level also. You might not be able to afford donating 50pp for a buff at level 20, but that's a drop in the bucket at 65 or 70.<br><br>I personally never ask for buffs anymore (don't really need them when I solo with my bard), but when I'm playing an alt... I'll donate 50pp for Virtue, 70 for Conviction, 20-30 for KEI... 20 for a port somewhere, 100-300 for a rez (typically only 100 now since you can summon corpses to the guild lobby).<br><br>Cleric AC/HP buffs don't cost reagents anymore, and the clarity line never has. It used to be common to see &quot;Casting Temp for donations, 12pp minimum to cover costs of peridots&quot;. That's not the case anymore. That does bring something else up though, a pet peeve of mine...<br><br>If you are casting buffs, and say it's for donations, don't expect a minimum donation. If you EXPECT a certain amount, say that in your advertisement. You're more then welcome to think your buff is worth X amount of pp, but if you only ask for donations, you can't get peeved when someone gives you 5pp.<br><br>That being said, for any type of action or buff that requires a reagent, you should be willing to at least pay for the reagent/supply your own and the time it may require your helper to help you. This used to be a big thing for necros and SK's, but not so much since we have the corpse summoners in the guild lobby. I can't tell you how many times people have asked my necro to help them summon a corpse from some way out of the way place that took me 20 minutes to get to, using a reagent that cost me 140pp, and then would give me 20pp and a &quot;thanks&quot;. I just saved them from having 20k+ worth of gear rotting, and got less in return then a cleric would for saving them a little experience... again, that's all pretty much moot now, with the corpse summoners, but I had to get it off my chest.<br><br>Anyway, the point is, donate what you think it is worth to you. Certain buffs are worth more to some then to others.</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br /><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006062&resize=true" target="akztarg">Jiggidyjay</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Ranger</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1003866&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zingin Ansinging</a> - <span class="sm">Mr Bard of <a href="HTTP://firestormers.com/viewnews.php" target="akztarg">The Firestormers</a></span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1006061&resize=true" target="akztarg">Zolotaya</a> - <span class="sm">Ms Necro</span class="sm"><br><a href="HTTP://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1189723" target="akztarg">Zeibis</a> - <span class="sm">Monk</span class="sm"></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from the Oval Office.</td></tr></table>
